 | A-099 | A template file is referenceable only when its immutable upload ledger labels it `document_category=template_source`, `related_entity_type=global`, and no related entity id; the actor holds the dedicated `documents.template.file_reference` permission. That authority is seeded only to the existing Compliance document-preparation owner and does not imply template read/manage or file download. All four source-defined sensitivity levels remain valid when the file row and upload ledger agree. | 008A2 requires global/template-source provenance, sensitivity validation, and an exact reference permission separate from read/manage/download, but the published upload contract has free-text provenance and the source RBAC catalogue names no atomic template-reference code or finer template sensitivity matrix. These narrow labels and permission avoid treating application/loan files or download capability as generation input without inventing a business mapping. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §§3/26.1-26.4; `docs/source/data-model.md` §§16.1-16.3; architecture review `2026-07-14_064206_architecture_review`; `docs/slices/008A2-template-effective-integrity-and-file-reference-boundary.md` | 008A2 and 008B | High | Yes | 2026-07-14 | If governance defines different provenance labels, eligible roles, or a narrower sensitivity matrix, update the single documents-owned reference decision and catalogue grant; never infer reference authority from file ids, metadata reads, or download permission. |
